		<description><![CDATA[First, don&#039;t get caught in fear, which makes you more vulnerable. You don&#039;t say what the traditions are but i wouldn&#039;t be able to advise you for those anyway. However, you are a child of Earth and can always turn to Nature for protection. Chant any prayer, any song that brings you close to the Sacred, calling and asking for help. Do it at least twice a day, it isn&#039;t about form, having some right words, but about the heartfelt call. Walk on the land. Offer a little tobacco to places where you feel the power is strong. Keep asking for help and guidance and protection. See yourself bathed in light, and all ill energies turned away from you, falling away and sinking into the earth. Wash yourself with salt water with the intention of clearing away the hateful energy, or with water perfumed with lavender or other essential oil. Sage is excellent for transforming negative forces; if it won&#039;t stay lit, persevere. You can either get the little charcoals for burning myrrh or you can make your own fire and use those coals. Don&#039;t be intimidated, your spiritual will and persistence will win out, can prevail, will prevail. It doesn&#039;t have to be sage, it could be mugwort which is the same family, or cedar or sweetgrass. Ask for help from your ancestors, or any Beings you hold sacred, ask for guidance in your dreams. Even better if you can find someone who holds sweatlodges, who knows what they&#039;re doing, and not connected with the hateful family. Take little patches of cloth, place tobacco into them and tie them up with prayers. Put them around your doorway, over or beside your bed. You can also take a cord, a new cord, yarn or string, smudge it, and tie knots in it to bind all energies intended to harm you. Put your prayers into the cord, and then place it somewhere, on your home altar, or in a tree hollow near your house, or in the ground outside your door. These are acts of intention that increase your spiritual protection. You have the power within you to turn this away, to send the energy back. You don&#039;t have to take it. Just have faith in whatever you hold most Sacred, Don&#039;t be afraid to ask for help from that Source. Play spiritual music in your home. Avoid people who might harm you, seek out positive allies. Ask for good people to come into your life. Most of all, calm yourself, don&#039;t panic, and take positive action with full faith.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>First, don&#8217;t get caught in fear, which makes you more vulnerable. You don&#8217;t say what the traditions are but i wouldn&#8217;t be able to advise you for those anyway. However, you are a child of Earth and can always turn to Nature for protection. Chant any prayer, any song that brings you close to the Sacred, calling and asking for help. Do it at least twice a day, it isn&#8217;t about form, having some right words, but about the heartfelt call. Walk on the land. Offer a little tobacco to places where you feel the power is strong. Keep asking for help and guidance and protection. See yourself bathed in light, and all ill energies turned away from you, falling away and sinking into the earth. Wash yourself with salt water with the intention of clearing away the hateful energy, or with water perfumed with lavender or other essential oil. Sage is excellent for transforming negative forces; if it won&#8217;t stay lit, persevere. You can either get the little charcoals for burning myrrh or you can make your own fire and use those coals. Don&#8217;t be intimidated, your spiritual will and persistence will win out, can prevail, will prevail. It doesn&#8217;t have to be sage, it could be mugwort which is the same family, or cedar or sweetgrass. Ask for help from your ancestors, or any Beings you hold sacred, ask for guidance in your dreams. Even better if you can find someone who holds sweatlodges, who knows what they&#8217;re doing, and not connected with the hateful family. Take little patches of cloth, place tobacco into them and tie them up with prayers. Put them around your doorway, over or beside your bed. You can also take a cord, a new cord, yarn or string, smudge it, and tie knots in it to bind all energies intended to harm you. Put your prayers into the cord, and then place it somewhere, on your home altar, or in a tree hollow near your house, or in the ground outside your door. These are acts of intention that increase your spiritual protection. You have the power within you to turn this away, to send the energy back. You don&#8217;t have to take it. Just have faith in whatever you hold most Sacred, Don&#8217;t be afraid to ask for help from that Source. Play spiritual music in your home. Avoid people who might harm you, seek out positive allies. Ask for good people to come into your life. Most of all, calm yourself, don&#8217;t panic, and take positive action with full faith.</p>
