		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.sourcememory.net/veleda/?p=63#comment-7185</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I am Native American with parents from two different tribes, and I was adopted by my biological mothers family.  I grew up knowing who my birth parents were and I knew that they were from two different tribes.  I found out years ago that my biological father&#039;s family hated my mother.  I was invited to spend a weekend with my bio-fathers mother and I chose to go to my bio-mother&#039;s wedding that same weekend.  My bio-grandma won&#039;t take my calls or respond back too me, as well as any family member from my fathers side. Recently I have been scratched on my legs and upper body. I have had 3 miscarriages and recently I was choked until I almost passed out.  Everytime my mom tries to smudge me the sage won&#039;t stay lit.  My mom believes that I have had a &quot;Bearwalk&quot; put on me, which in my tribe is a curse from someone who wants to do great bodily harm on you.  I am just looking for advice on what I should do. Please.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I am Native American with parents from two different tribes, and I was adopted by my biological mothers family.  I grew up knowing who my birth parents were and I knew that they were from two different tribes.  I found out years ago that my biological father&#8217;s family hated my mother.  I was invited to spend a weekend with my bio-fathers mother and I chose to go to my bio-mother&#8217;s wedding that same weekend.  My bio-grandma won&#8217;t take my calls or respond back too me, as well as any family member from my fathers side. Recently I have been scratched on my legs and upper body. I have had 3 miscarriages and recently I was choked until I almost passed out.  Everytime my mom tries to smudge me the sage won&#8217;t stay lit.  My mom believes that I have had a &#8220;Bearwalk&#8221; put on me, which in my tribe is a curse from someone who wants to do great bodily harm on you.  I am just looking for advice on what I should do. Please.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
