		<description><![CDATA[&quot;White male sources&quot; will continue to talk and say what they will, but we as Anishinaabe don&#039;t worry about this, that is, if we truly understand ourselves through our world view as expressed through our language...

Basically, if you had asked a speaker, they would have told you that the term you were researching could apply to either a male or female, instead of trying to dig through documents only.

My understanding of that term is &quot;One of the dawn,&quot; again, no direct correlation to any one sex. Knowing the language of a people goes much further than one might think...]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>&#8220;White male sources&#8221; will continue to talk and say what they will, but we as Anishinaabe don&#8217;t worry about this, that is, if we truly understand ourselves through our world view as expressed through our language&#8230;</p>
<p>Basically, if you had asked a speaker, they would have told you that the term you were researching could apply to either a male or female, instead of trying to dig through documents only.</p>
<p>My understanding of that term is &#8220;One of the dawn,&#8221; again, no direct correlation to any one sex. Knowing the language of a people goes much further than one might think&#8230;</p>
